title: $A higher in quiet trade
text:
Fri, Jul 17, 2015, 1:12 PM AEST - Australia Markets close in 2 hrs 48 mins $A higher in quiet trade AAP â€“ 40 minutes ago Print 
The Australian dollar is stronger against a greenback that has been dented by disappointing US economic data. 
At 1200 AEST on Friday, the currency was trading at 74.13 US cents, up from 73.81 US cents on Thursday. 
The Aussie dollar's value against the US dollar was boosted overnight by the release of downbeat data on US businesses. 
The Philadelphia Federal Reserve business outlook index fell from 15.2 to 5.7, below expectations. 
With very little local news on Friday, currency traders are looking ahead to US inflation data for June due out Friday night. 
KEY MOVEMENTS: 
* 74.13 US cents, from 73.81 cents on Thursday 
* 92.01 Japanese yen, from 91.39 yen 
* 68.05 euro cents, from 67.52 euro cents 
* 113.49 New Zealand cents, from 113.10 NZ cents 
* 47.46 British pence, from 47.23 pence 
Government bond yields: 
* CGS 5.5pct Jan 2018, 1.966%, from 1.951%, on Thursday 
* CGS 4.25pct April 2026, 3.052%, from 3.057% 
* Sept 2015 10-year bond futures contract at 96.990 (yield 3.010 pct), up from 96.985 (3.015 pct) 
* Sept 2015 3-year bond futures contract at 97.960 (2.040 pct), up from 97.980 (2.020 per cent) 
(*Currency closes taken at 1700 AEST previous local session, bond market closes taken at 1630 AEST previous local session) 
Source: IRESS
